title: For Sale:  Kel-Tec KSG 12 ga
location: MKTactical LLC Guns and Training in Hillsboro, Oregon, United States
postcontent:
We will ship to your FFL ($35)

Call us at REDACTED

The KSG (Kel-Tec Shotgun) is Kel-Tec CNC’s first entry into the shotgun market. The size, shape, and design is similar to the currently available Kel-Tec RFB rifle, but the KSG ejects downward, instead of forward. The KSG weighs 6.9 lbs. and is as compact as legally possible with a 26.1” overall length and an 18.5” cylinder bore barrel. Even with this compact size, the internal dual tube magazines hold an impressive 12 rounds of 12 gauge 3” rounds in total (6 per tube). It can also reliably shoot shells as short as 1 3/4" up to the 3".
This simple and reliable pump action feeds from either the left or right tube. The feed side is manually selected by a lever located behind the trigger guard.

The pump includes an under picatinny rail for the mounting of a forward grip, a light, or a laser. The included top picatinny sight rail will accept many types of optics or iron sights. Forward and rear sling loops are built in, and a basic sling is included. The soft rubber butt pad helps to tame recoil.

The KSG receiver is made from hardened steel and includes the magazine tubes which have been welded in place. The grip and stock assembly is made of glass reinforced nylon (Zytel) and is easily disassembled by pushing out 2 pins, which store in 2 holes in the grip when removed. The barrel and pump assembly is removed by loosening the 2 front magazine tube nuts with a coin and sliding the assembly forward.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Ex Sniper mosin nagant
postcontent:
This is a mosin that was once a sniper during Wwii,  meaning it was picked out of a batch due to its accuracy and made into a sniper. 

After Wwii the excess amount of snipers cause Russia to remove the scope,  fill in the hole with threaded plugs,  and do a shallow weld on them. 

From the inside of the receiver the plugs can be seen,  from the outside,  only a trained eye can spot them. 

This rifle still has its old scope numbers on the side of it. 

Every number matches on this rifle,  and the bore is excellent.

title: For Sale:  Winchester Model 70 Featherweight .270 WSM 2008 Limited Edition
postcontent:
If you known your guns, you know this is one of if not THE best hunting rifles of all time. And the best of these rifles were thought to be the pre 1964 guns until 2008. In 2008, Winchester redesigned the Model 70 and went back to the better (and more expensive) building methods (aka pre 1964). This gun is the best of the best. It was made in 2008 and it's a Limited Edition 2008 which comes with a beautiful marble-walnut stock. 
Another important note about Model 70's. In 2013, Winchester decided to stop assembling the model 70's in the USA. That's right, any new Model 70 is now assembled in Portugal. 5+ years from now, the guns made from 2008-2013 will command a premium in their Portuguese assembled brethren.

About THIS gun! It's a 2008 Limited Edition Winchester Model 70 .270 WSM. It'll be perfect for ANY type of hunting in North America. It's NEVER BEEN FIRED, and the condition reflects this. There's a TINY nick on the bottom of the stock, and a little rubbing of the bluing on the barrel from sitting in the safe, but it's been repaired. I'm selling it because I think I'd rather have something that I wouldn't feel bad about dinging up when I go hunting. 
I believe my price of $650 is very fair, as this gun was over $1000 brand new.

For more info, call Jorgen at REDACTED

postcontent:
TAURUS PT 38S Automatic Pistol. DOUBLE ACTION . AMBIDEXTROUS DE-Cocker Type SAFETY.Parkerized. Based on Beretta PT series but with SQUARE METAL FULL COVER  SLIDE like Glocks .  Comes with 2 Magazines. It is a LIGHTER WEIGHT GUN than the BERETTA PT 92 ,thus not as COMBERSOME to CARRY.
 You CAN Convert this Gun to 9mm Luger with JUST a BARRELL CHANGE!
   It is Based on the PT 92 Series but with  a Squared top Slide. Adjustable rear Sight, AMBIDEXTROUS DE-COCKER Type SAFETY (OH GOODY!)  and the SLIDE in MY OPINION OFFERS MUCH BETTER grip on it than MANY HANDGUNS !  IT CAN BE CARRIED " COCKED & LOCKED " Just like a 1911 except that the TAURUS PT 38S is a DOUBLE ACTION Pistol !
 The Sights are nice SQUARE COMBAT STYLE and the FLAT TOP SLIDE with these sights enable a FAST SIGHT ACQUISITION ! The Gun has had More Holster wear than Shooting Wear.
 It seems to be a LIGHTER GUN than Most Big Autos and is really EASIER to carry Around as it DOESN'T WEIGH a TON !! 
       The .38 SUPER HITS HARDER than 9MM Luger Round as the BULLET IS HEAVIER and a Bit FASTER!
 Comes with 2 Magazines and 1 box of 50 Winchester Silvertip HOLLOW POINT  Ammo and one box of 9mm Largo which is the same as the old COLT .38 Auto except with a Pointier Bullet  ( but I grind off the very end of the POINTY BULLET TIPS about 3mm as the Pointier Copper Round needs to be a tad shorter to fit in the Magazine.). Then they work fine . The 9mm Largo are cheaper than .38 SUPER so for Plinking they are fine.
  You CAN Convert this Gun to 9mm Luger with JUST a BARREL CHANGE!
 HOWEVER the 38 SUPER  is a longer Cartridge and can be Hand Loaded to much Higher Velocities than 9mm Luger..38 SUPER has a HEAVIER BULLET than 9mm Luger so even if they were going the SAME SPEED the .38 SUPER DELIVERS MORE POWER! 
 It is generally Only Loaded toSlightly Higher Speeds than 9mm Luger as the .38 Super uses the SAME CASE as the Old COLT .38 Automatic and Manufacturers stopped loading the .38 Super to it's REAL POTENTIAL after many Shooters Fired .38 SUPER in OLDER COLT .38 AUTOMATICS and BLEW THEM UP! 
 Think of the ORIGINAL .38 SUPER as a .38 AUTOMATIC MAGNUM or .357 MAGNUM!!  Guns Chambered for and Made for the OLD .38 AUTOMATIC round were DISCONTINUED in 1939 due to WW2 1911 Colt .45 Automatic contracts. 
    .38 AUTOMATIC WAS a VERY POPULAR HANDGUN in the CIVILIAN MARKET but  it was in Production in some form of COLT AUTOMATIC since 1900 (!!!! ) .
  BUT the .38 AUTOMATICS COULD NOT TAKE THE .38 SUPER ROUND!!
    SO,.. ANOTHER GREAT IDEA ( the HIGH VELOCITY  .38 SUPER Round ) HURT by Consumers BEING DUMBSH-TS!! 

$350

title: For Sale:  Eotech 552 Holographic Optic
postcontent:
Looking to sell my Eotech 552 Holographic optic.

Optic has sat mounted to a rifle, carried some but rarely shot, minor paint/finish wear, glass perfect, clear view and very easy to shoot with, no problems with use.

Per Eotech's website, ways to spot a knockoff include:

*Uncommon batteries. The Counterfeit products often, but not always require several small hearing aid style batteries
(Uses AA batteries)

* A product that offers interchangeable Red and Green reticle colors
(Red reticle only)

* Highly reflective optics
(Non-"highly reflective optic")

* Visible LED light position inside the sight cavity
(No LED visible inside sight cavity)

* The NV push button switches the LED to a different color instead of to a night vision mode
(NV button puts optic in NV mode, not other color)

* Lack of EOTech manufacturing and serial number sticker
(Has EOTech manufacturing and serial number stick)

http://www.eotechinc.com/counterfeit-alert-how-to-spot-a-fake

New Eotech 552's are going for $530-550 on eBay. Looking for $450 obo, sale via a face to face transaction in the Klamath Falls area with a cash or PayPal payment, or shipped anywhere in the U.S. for actual shipping cost with payment via PayPal only.
